The paper is about a domain-specific language (DSL) for deep learning, which involves programming languages (cs.PL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus is on the optimization and efficiency of the compiled code, which relates to software engineering (cs.SE) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the DSL with various deep learning networks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
